I"w<h2 id="parts-1-2-overview">Parts 1-2 Overview</h2>
<ul>
  <li>How to center your images and maintain aspect ratio?
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://developer.android.com/reference/android/widget/ImageView.ScaleType">This documentation</a> may be of help.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Remember to give all images an ID number!</li>
  <li>Margin value is given to you (vMargin)</li>
  <li>There should also be more pre-set values that you can use, no need to use <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magic_number_(programming)">Magic Numbers</a></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="parts-3-4-overview">Parts 3-4 Overview</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Remember to <strong>add your ConstraintLayout to Part2View</strong> –&gt; using addView(…)</li>
  <li>What does <a href="https://developer.android.com/reference/android/view/LayoutInflater">“inflate”</a> mean?
    <ul>
      <li>Layout XML -&gt; create view objects in memory, allowing you to later add &amp; modify stuff w/ Java
then add this view (the whole XML) to activity on runtime.</li>
      <li><em>inflate(int resource, ViewGroup root)</em></li>
      <li>resource is the XML file you want to inflate</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Your “imitation” layout should look very similar to the website/app you’re trying to copy
    <ul>
      <li>You may get docked if it isn’t similar enough… (missing buttons, labels, etc)</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
